In mathematics, '''eigenvalue perturbation''' is a [[perturbation theory|perturbation]] approach to finding [[Eigenvector|eigenvalues and eigenvectors]] of systems perturbed from one with known eigenvectors and eigenvalues. It also allows one to determine the sensitivity of the eigenvalues and eigenvectors with respect to changes in the system. The following derivations are essentially self-contained and can be found in many texts on numerical linear algebra<ref name="Trefethen258">{{cite book |title=Numerical Linear Algebra |last=Trefethen |first=Lloyd N. |year=1997 |publisher=SIAM (Philadelphia, PA) |isbn=0-89871-361-7 |page=258 }}</ref>  or numerical functional analysis.
